President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Justice Geoffrey W. Crawford to serve on the United States District Court for the District of Vermont. Justice Crawford currently serves as an Associate Justice on the Vermont Supreme Court and previously served as a judge on the Vermont Superior Court. He has a long and distinguished record of service in the legal field, including working at various law firms and serving as a law clerk to Judge Albert W. Coffrin. Justice Crawford received his J.D. from Harvard Law School and his B.A. from Yale University.